- the	regulatory	and	business	risks	associated	with	participation	in	certain	government	health	care	programs,	including	the Medicare	Shared	Savings	Program	through	Signify	Health's	Caravan	accountable	care	organizations	('ACOs')	and identification	of	diagnosis	codes	related	to	risk	adjustment	payments	under	Part	C	of	the	Medicare	program;
